const title = "Pizza Oven Repair Los Angeles — Same Day";
const description = "Residential outdoor pizza oven repair across SoCal. Gas burner, stone deck, insulation, ignition. Ooni, Forno, Alfa, Gozney. BHGS #A49573. $120 dx.";

const faqs = [
  {
    q: "Do you service Ooni Karu, Koda, and Pro models?",
    a: "Yes. Most Ooni service work involves the gas burner module on Koda and Karu gas-converted models (igniter, regulator, burner orifice), plus stone deck cracking from thermal shock. We see this 4 to 6 times a month from LA backyard owners. $120 outdoor diagnostic; Ooni parts are inexpensive ($40 to $280 typical) and well-stocked through Ooni's US distribution network. Honest framing: at year 6+ on a budget Ooni unit (Fyra, Karu 12, Koda 12), if the gas valve assembly fails, you're looking at $200+ in repair on a $300 to $500 unit. We tell you straight whether replacement makes more sense."
  },
  {
    q: "What's the difference between residential outdoor and commercial pizza oven repair?",
    a: "Commercial pizza ovens (deck, conveyor, brick, impinger) are completely different equipment. Higher BTU output, three-phase electrical, gas line pressure regulators sized for restaurant volume, refractory brick rebuilds. We service those through our commercial pizza oven repair line; that's a different service tier and different diagnostic process. This page is for residential backyard outdoor pizza ovens: portable units, built-in luxury units, DIY kits. If you're a restaurant operator, see <a href='/commercial/pizza-oven-repair/'>commercial pizza oven repair</a>."
  },
  {
    q: "Is wood-fired pizza oven use legal in Southern California?",
    a: "Outdoor cooking equipment, including wood-fired pizza ovens, is generally permitted in Southern California. SCAQMD Rule 445 restricts new indoor wood-burning fireplaces and pellet stoves in residential dwellings; that rule does not target outdoor cooking equipment. Local jurisdictions may require permits for permanent built-in installations, and during high-pollution advisories (Spare the Air days) voluntary restrictions apply. Most of our customers run multi-fuel units (Ooni Karu, Gozney Dome) on gas during advisory days and wood otherwise."
  },
  {
    q: "How long do built-in luxury pizza ovens last?",
    a: "Alfresco AXE-30, Lynx Professional, Wolf outdoor: 12 to 18 years with maintenance. Stone hearth typically lasts 10 to 15 years before needing rotation or replacement. Gas burner modules go year 7 to 12. Refractory cement ceiling repairs at year 8 to 12. The units significantly outlast portable Ooni and Gozney equivalents because of commercial-grade insulation, heavier-gauge construction, and serviceable component design."
  },
  {
    q: "My Alfresco AXE pizza oven won't reach 700°F anymore. Why?",
    a: "Three usual causes: insulation degradation in the dome (refractory cement cracked, year 8 to 12 typical), gas valve regulating below spec (manometer test confirms), or stone hearth absorbing moisture from inactive winter months (run a 2-hour dry cycle to drive moisture out). We test all three at the $120 diagnostic. Insulation rebuild $440 to $780. Gas valve replacement $260 to $440. Stone moisture cycle no parts required."
  },
  {
    q: "What's your warranty?",
    a: "90 days SDAR labor warranty on every repair. BHGS #A49573 and EPA 608 Universal certified (#1346255700410). BBB A+ accredited."
  },
  {
    q: "Do you do new pizza oven installations?",
    a: "We don't do new outdoor kitchen construction or built-in pizza oven installation. We service what's already installed. For new builds we work with several Beverly Hills, Calabasas, and Pacific Palisades outdoor kitchen contractors and can refer. Portable Ooni and Gozney unboxing assistance: we'll come out at $120, set up, run the first burn-in, and inspect for shipping damage if requested, but standard customer assembly is straightforward and most owners don't need us for that."
  }
];

