<!-- 01 INTRO + INTENT DISAMBIGUATION -->
<section class="section">
  <div class="container narrow">
    <p class="section-number">01 · Residential outdoor pizza oven repair</p>
    <h2 class="section-title">Three product tiers, one license, one diagnostic.</h2>

    <p>This page covers <strong>residential outdoor pizza oven repair</strong>. Backyard portable units, built-in luxury hearths, DIY kits. If you're a restaurant operator running a deck oven, conveyor, or brick rebuild, you're on the wrong page. See <a href="/commercial/pizza-oven-repair/">commercial pizza oven repair</a> for those. The two services use different parts pipelines, different gas line pressure work, and different diagnostic processes.</p>

    <p>The residential outdoor pizza oven market in Los Angeles, Orange, and Ventura counties has grown sharply since 2022. We see new Ooni and Gozney unboxings every week, plus built-in Alfresco and Lynx units in Beverly Hills, Calabasas, Hidden Hills, Newport Coast, and Pacific Palisades outdoor kitchens. The repair load tracks the install curve: most failures show up at year 3 to 8 depending on tier and exposure.</p>

    <p>Our service split by tier:</p>
    <ul class="bullet-list">
      <li><strong>Portable backyard ($300 to $1,500 unit):</strong> Ooni Karu (multi-fuel), Ooni Koda (gas), Ooni Fyra (pellet), Ooni Pro (legacy multi-fuel), Gozney Roccbox (gas), Gozney Dome (multi-fuel). Lower repair tier, parts $40 to $280, year 6 replace conversation common.</li>
      <li><strong>Built-in luxury ($4,000 to $8,000+ unit):</strong> Alfresco AXE-30 (gas, stone hearth), Lynx Professional pizza oven (gas), Wolf outdoor pizza oven (gas). Premium repair tier, parts $260 to $1,200, year 12 to 18 service life with maintenance.</li>
      <li><strong>DIY kits and pre-built brick ($2,000 to $12,000):</strong> Forno Bravo, Earthstone, Mugnaini. Refractory rebuilds, chimney work, gas conversion services for previously wood-only units.</li>
    </ul>

    <p><strong>$120 outdoor commercial-tier diagnostic, waived with repair.</strong> BHGS #A49573 and EPA 608 Universal certified (#1346255700410). 90-day warranty. Same-day across LA, OC, Ventura.</p>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- 02 WOOD-FIRED, GAS-FIRED, MULTI-FUEL -->
<section class="section section-gray">
  <div class="container narrow">
    <p class="section-number">02 · Wood-fired vs gas-fired vs multi-fuel</p>
    <h2 class="section-title">Outdoor cooking equipment is treated differently from indoor fireplaces.</h2>

    <p>Wood-fired pizza ovens are common questions. Customers worry about SCAQMD Rule 445 because they've heard about wood-burning restrictions. Quick clarification:</p>

    <ul class="bullet-list">
      <li><strong>SCAQMD Rule 445 targets indoor wood-burning fireplaces and pellet stoves</strong> in residential dwellings. New construction restrictions on these fixtures cover indoor heating equipment in living spaces.</li>
      <li><strong>Outdoor cooking equipment is a different category.</strong> Backyard wood-fired pizza ovens, charcoal grills, smokers, and similar outdoor cooking units are generally permitted under SCAQMD framework.</li>
      <li><strong>Local jurisdictions may require permits</strong> for permanent built-in installations, particularly in fire-zone areas (Malibu, Topanga, hillside Pacific Palisades, Calabasas). We always recommend confirming local permit requirements before built-in construction.</li>
      <li><strong>Spare the Air voluntary restrictions</strong> apply on high-pollution advisory days. Most of our customers with multi-fuel units (Ooni Karu, Gozney Dome) run gas on advisory days and wood otherwise.</li>
    </ul>

    <p>Multi-fuel units (Ooni Karu series, Ooni Pro, Gozney Dome) give owners flexibility to switch fuel sources. We service all fuel modes; the gas burner accessory module is the most-serviced component on multi-fuel Ooni and Gozney units.</p>

    <p>Pure gas units (Ooni Koda, Gozney Roccbox, Alfresco AXE-30, Lynx Professional, Wolf outdoor) skip the wood/charcoal complexity and tend to run cleaner. The trade-off is no real wood-fire flavor. The market has moved decisively toward gas in built-in luxury and split roughly 60/40 gas/multi-fuel in portable.</p>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- 03 COMMON FAILURES -->
<section class="section">
  <div class="container narrow">
    <p class="section-number">03 · Common failures we see</p>
    <h2 class="section-title">By tier, by component.</h2>

    <div class="cause-block">
      <h3>1. Gas burner igniter (year 3-5)</h3>
      <p>Most common service call across both portable gas units (Ooni Koda, Gozney Roccbox) and built-in luxury (Alfresco AXE-30, Lynx Professional). Spark electrode fails or ignition control module fatigues. Portable replacement $40 to $140. Built-in $200 to $440 depending on brand.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="cause-block">
      <h3>2. Stone deck cracking (year 5-8 portable, year 10-15 built-in)</h3>
      <p>Stone hearth absorbs moisture during inactive months, then cracks from thermal stress when fired up cold. Common on portable Ooni stones left outside through winter. Built-in stones last longer because of better insulation but eventually need rotation or replacement. Portable stone $40 to $90 (DIY-friendly part). Built-in stone $260 to $560.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="cause-block">
      <h3>3. Insulation refractory degradation (year 8-12 built-in only)</h3>
      <p>Refractory cement in the dome ceiling cracks over years of thermal cycling. Symptom: oven won't reach 700°F+ even with gas burner running full. Insulation rebuild on Alfresco AXE, Lynx Professional, Wolf outdoor: $440 to $780 labor plus refractory materials. Built-in luxury repair tier always justified through year 12 to 15.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="cause-block">
      <h3>4. Wood-fire chimney and exhaust issues</h3>
      <p>Wood-fired and multi-fuel units develop creosote buildup, chimney corrosion, and exhaust path obstruction over years. Annual cleaning service $180 to $260. Chimney/flue replacement on built-in $340 to $680 depending on brand and configuration.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="cause-block">
      <h3>5. Gas valve assembly fatigue (year 5-8 portable, year 8-12 built-in)</h3>
      <p>Manifold pressure regulator and burner valve drift over time. Symptom: low flame, slow heat-up, won't hold target temp. Manometer test at the burner inlet confirms. Portable $80 to $160. Built-in $260 to $440.</p>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- 04 REPAIR-VS-REPLACE TIER MATH -->
<section class="section section-gray">
  <div class="container narrow">
    <p class="section-number">04 · Repair-vs-replace by tier (honest math)</p>
    <h2 class="section-title">Ooni year 6 is different from Alfresco year 15.</h2>

    <p>The repair-vs-replace conversation depends on tier. We tell customers straight at the diagnostic which side of the line their unit sits on.</p>

    <p><strong>Portable budget tier (Ooni Fyra, Ooni Karu 12, Ooni Koda 12, Gozney Roccbox):</strong></p>
    <ul class="bullet-list">
      <li>Year 0 to 4: any failure is a repair. Parts cheap, unit value high.</li>
      <li>Year 5 to 7: depends on the failure. Stone replacement, igniter, simple gas valve = repair. Full burner module + control board failure on a $400 unit = replace conversation.</li>
      <li>Year 8+: usually replace. Most portable units are at end-of-life by then.</li>
    </ul>

    <p><strong>Portable mid-tier (Ooni Karu 16, Ooni Koda 16, Ooni Pro 16, Gozney Dome):</strong></p>
    <ul class="bullet-list">
      <li>Year 0 to 7: repair. Unit value $700 to $1,500, parts $40 to $280, math works.</li>
      <li>Year 8 to 10: case-by-case. Major failures push toward replace.</li>
    </ul>

    <p><strong>Built-in luxury (Alfresco AXE-30, Lynx Professional, Wolf outdoor):</strong></p>
    <ul class="bullet-list">
      <li>Year 0 to 12: always repair. Unit value $4,000 to $8,000+, parts $260 to $1,200, repair always justified.</li>
      <li>Year 13 to 18: still usually repair. Insulation rebuild + gas valve refresh extends service life 5 to 7 years.</li>
      <li>Year 18+: case-by-case based on cabinet condition and broader outdoor kitchen plans.</li>
    </ul>

    <p>We don't push repair on units that should be replaced. We don't push replace on units that should be repaired. Honest math at $120 dx.</p>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- 05 LA LUXURY MARKET -->
<section class="section">
  <div class="container narrow">
    <p class="section-number">05 · LA luxury outdoor kitchen market</p>
    <h2 class="section-title">Built-in pizza ovens are the fastest-growing outdoor category since 2022.</h2>

    <p>Outdoor entertainment investment in Los Angeles County has shifted toward integrated outdoor kitchens with built-in pizza ovens since the pandemic-era home upgrade cycle. New construction and remodels in Beverly Hills, Bel Air, Pacific Palisades, Brentwood, Calabasas, Hidden Hills, Newport Coast, and Newport Beach increasingly include a built-in pizza oven alongside the grill, refrigeration, and prep area.</p>

    <p>Most-installed built-in models we service:</p>
    <ul class="bullet-list">
      <li><strong>Alfresco AXE-30.</strong> Most common premium choice in our service area. 30-inch stone hearth, gas-fired, $4,000 to $6,000 unit cost. Made by BBQG Inc. (Commerce, CA), serviced through Alfresco's parts pipeline. See our <a href="/outdoor/pizza-oven-repair/brands/alfresco/">Alfresco AXE service page</a>.</li>
      <li><strong>Lynx Professional pizza oven.</strong> Stone hearth, gas-fired premium tier from Lynx (Compton, CA). Pairs with Lynx grill installations.</li>
      <li><strong>Wolf outdoor pizza oven.</strong> Sub-Zero Group authorized service path. Pairs with Wolf outdoor grill installations in matched outdoor kitchens.</li>
      <li><strong>Forno Bravo, Earthstone, Mugnaini.</strong> Italian-style refractory builds in DIY-kit or pre-built form. Pre-2018 installations now seeing refractory rebuild work.</li>
    </ul>

    <p>Most-installed portable models we service:</p>
    <ul class="bullet-list">
      <li><strong>Ooni.</strong> UK-based, founded 2012 (Edinburgh, originally Uuni). Karu, Koda, Fyra, Pro, Volt model lines. See our <a href="/outdoor/pizza-oven-repair/brands/ooni/">Ooni service page</a>.</li>
      <li><strong>Gozney.</strong> UK-based as well. Roccbox (gas, portable) and Dome (multi-fuel, semi-portable) model lines.</li>
    </ul>
  </div>
</section>

